benchmark_config.jira_title: Implement/Test API: GET /1.0/kb/customFields/search/{searchKey} - Search custom fields

covered: GET Valid Request scenarios are exercised (TC01, TC02, TC03, TC04, TC05, TC06, TC07, TC08, TC09, TC10, TC11, TC12, TC13, TC14, TC18, TC30).
Empty Response handling is addressed (TC01 with potential empty results, TC06).
Pagination scenarios are covered (TC02 with limit/offset, TC07/TC08).
Query Parameters coverage includes limit, offset, audit, and extra parameters (TC02, TC03, TC04, TC05, TC10, TC11, TC12, TC13, TC14, TC18, TC28, TC29, TC30).
Error handling for bad inputs and service issues covered (TC11, TC12, TC13, TC14, TC17, TC30).
Backward compatibility and legacy behavior included (TC22).
Integration/data consistency and documentation aspects touched (TC23, TC24).
XSS/injection and input validation considerations included (TC18, TC25, TC26, TC27).
Boundary and stress tests included (TC09, TC07, TC19).
Method correctness including unsupported method tested (TC30).
gaps: Rate limiting tests are not present (guideline mentions rate limiting).
Explicit 403/invalid auth detail scenarios beyond 401 are not described (authorization failures beyond token issues).
Comprehensive error response structure validation across all error scenarios is not deeply explicit in tests (only general).
Performance metrics (e.g., response time thresholds) are only in TC19; broader SLA checks could be added.
recommendations: Add dedicated rate-limiting/throttling tests to verify system behavior under rapid succession of requests.
Introduce tests that verify caching headers (ETag, Cache-Control) and cache reuse behavior across requests.
Enhance authorization edge-case testing (e.g., 403 for insufficient permissions, token expiry handling).
Expand error payload validation to ensure consistent error schema across all error cases (structure, codes, messages).
Add explicit performance regression tests for typical and peak loads beyond TC19 (e.g., 95th percentile latency, SLA targets).
Include more explicit tests for edge-case inputs (very long searchKey lengths, Unicode edge cases, whitespace-only keys) with deterministic expectations.
